## Protocols

### Authorization Ladder

| Level | Ops | Gate |
|-------|-----|------|
| G0 | Read, RO reports | — |
| G1 | Edit WT, plans, impl (no commit) | Transition gate |
| G2-code | `git commit` **code only** (`src/`, `web/`, `tests/`) | Step 7 / 10 / 11 fix |
| G2-delivery | `git commit` **`{slug}.plan.md` + `{slug}.result.md` only** | Step 12 delivery gate |
| G3 | `git push`, PR | Step 12 consent; PR manual |

```text
HS-1: AskQuestion cancelled → STOP; re-present gate. Never infer "yes".
HS-2: Commit without explicit gate menu selection → STOP.
HS-2a: `git add` or commit any `.cursor/plans/` path during Steps 0–11 → STOP (workflow artifacts forbidden until Step 12 delivery commit).
HS-3: Mutating step success + empty files_touched → FAILED.
HS-4: Step 5/10/11 success without expected files on state.branch → FAILED.
HS-5: State Hygiene failed → STOP before Progress Board.
```
Auto: HS-3/4/5 apply; HS-1/2 N/A.

### Transition Discipline

**Normal:** N done → Hygiene → checkpoint `before-step-{N+1}` → Board → summary → Transition Gate → then dispatch N+1 (resume "continue" same turn OK).

**Auto:** auto-gate + dispatch N+1 same turn.

**Forbidden:** mutating step or commit without gate.

### Refinement FSM (Step 2)

2a/2b/2d → `02-refine`. Orch: 2c Escalate, 2e Shared Understanding, redispatch.

| State | Owner | Output |
|-------|-------|--------|
| 2a Audit | refine | `gap_registry[]` by design-tree |
| 2b Resolve | refine | Close with evidence; codebase before escalate |
| 2c Escalate | orch | AskQuestion — **one** question; max 3 rounds; always **End refinement and advance** |
| 2d Exit | refine | §8 empty or `assumed-default`; `shared_understanding: pending` |
| 2e Shared Understanding | orch | **I confirm shared understanding — advance to Step 3** / **Continue refinement** |

Rules: multiple `needs_user` → one by design-tree priority. **End refinement** → log `assumed-default`, gate 2e (not Step 3). Block Step 3 if `refine.shared_understanding !== confirmed`.

### Worktree Fallback

```text
dryRun → no worktree
win32 OR path>180 OR git worktree add fails → branch-direct (log ## Gate history)
else → step-worktree
```

branch-direct: edits on `state.branch`; subagent `wip(us-{id}): step-{N}` or dirty WT. Post-step 5/10/11: files exist, expected diff, build/tests per stack.md.

### State Hygiene

After step N, before board. `Read` → `Write`/`StrReplace` → `Glob` asserts. Fail → HS-5.

```yaml
- Check modelChain[N+1] → if set, update currentModel and log model-chain in ## Gate history
- Append ## Step outputs ### Step N (include model: {modelName} in block)
- Append step-output.learning → ## Workflow memory (dedupe: check existing entries first)
- Merge files_touched → ## Step file log ### Step N
- Append to ## Step model log: | Step N | {label} | {model} | dispatched {ISO} |
- Record telemetry: elapsedMs, promptTokens, completionTokens, estimated → ## Telemetry ### Step N
- Append to ## Telemetry log: | Step N | {label} | {model} | {elapsedMs}ms | {tokens} |
- Recompute workflowManifest; update completedSteps, stepStatus, currentStep
- Append stepDispatches; commits[] if commit
- Assert created paths exist; currentStep = next gate
- Step 2: ## Refinement registry
```

### Model Readiness Sub-gates

Steps **4†,8†** remain as **model sub-gates** embedded in transitions F1→F2 (post-3) and F3→F4 (post-7). Unlike the general per-step model switch, these sub-gates recommend a specific model class (Coder for F2, Reviewer/thinking for F4) and gate the phase transition explicitly.

Log: `model-gate | F1→F2|F3→F4 | current | recommended | choice | ISO`.

**F1→F2 (after Step 3):** implementing code next.

```text
Current model: {currentModel}
Recommended for coding (Steps 5, 10): Coder-class models

Options:
- Switch to {recommended-coder-model} and advance to Step 5 (Recommended)
- Keep {currentModel} and advance to Step 5
- Choose a different model and advance
- Repeat Step 3
- Go back / Pause
```

**F3→F4 (after Step 7):** review phase next.

```text
Current model: {currentModel}
Recommended for review (Steps 9, 10): Thinking/Reviewer-class models

Options:
- Switch to {recommended-reviewer-model} and advance to Step 9 (Recommended)
- Keep {currentModel} and advance to Step 9
- Choose a different model and advance
- Repeat Step 7
- Go back / Pause
```

Tags `before-step-5`, `before-step-9` at transitions. The orchestrator resolves `{recommended-*-model}` to an actual available model name — never present "Coder class" or "Reviewer class" to the user; always show concrete model names.

**Per-step model switch** (available at every transition gate, steps 0→1 through 11→12): the **Switch model and advance** option lets the user pick any model before dispatching the next step, without the phase-level recommendation. The model sub-gates at 4†/8† augment this with a class-level recommendation and concrete model suggestion.

### Step Dispatch & Isolation

Orchestrator calls **`Task`** — never inline step impl.

```yaml
Task:
  subagent_type: generalPurpose | shell
  description: "US-WF step {N} — {Label}"
  readonly: true   # step 6 only
  run_in_background: false   # step 5 parallel (DAG): ≤3 parallel, same worktree, no file overlap
  # step 5 sequential: single Task, no parallelism
  # resume: FORBIDDEN across steps
```

Anchor (`Shell` tag): `uswf/{workflow-id}/before-step-{N} @ {sha}`. Worktree 5/10/11 via `Shell`: `worktree add` → merge → `worktree remove` → `branch -d`. Max 1 active. Audit: `Write` `stepDispatches[]`. No per-DAG-task worktree.

**Step 5 dispatch:**
- `execMode: sequential` → single `Task` `04-implement-plan` mode `build` with `{slug}.plan.md` directly (no DAG). Implementation reads section 3 and executes step-by-step sequentially.
- `execMode: parallel` → existing DAG behavior: `Task` per level, ≤3 concurrent, no file overlap within level.

### Memory Consultation

Every step start, the subagent MUST read from state.

**Pre-read checklist (mandatory before first action):**

| Source | Section | Purpose |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `state.md` | `## Workflow memory` | Traps, gotchas, fixes logged by prior steps — **do not repeat mistakes** |
| `state.md` | `## Accumulated decisions` | Design choices, assumption flags, deviations from plan |
| `state.md` | `## Step outputs` (all `### Step N` blocks) | Prior errors, retry patterns, broken approaches |
| `state.md` | `## Doc consolidation log` | Docs updated during this workflow |
| `MEMORY.md` | Index + scope-related sections | Generalizable anti-regression patterns from past workflows |
| `check_memory_conflict.py` | script output | Conflict detection (steps 2,3,5,9,10) |

**Learning from prior steps:** before coding or deciding, scan `## Step outputs ### Step N` blocks for `errors[]` and `learning` fields. If a prior step hit a trap (bad query pattern, wrong EF API, incorrect hook usage), avoid it. The state file IS the intra-workflow knowledge bus.

**Writing back:** after step completion, record in `step-output.learning`:
- Mistakes made in this step and how they were fixed
- Traps discovered (wrong approach that cost time)
- New constraints discovered (API limitations, framework quirks)
- These are promoted to `MEMORY.md` at Step 12 if generalizable

### Specification Protocol

[`spec-format`](../spec-format/SKILL.md). Canonical spec: `{us-dir}/{slug}.spec.md` — never GitHub API or `*.issue.json`.

| Input | Action |
|-------|--------|
| `{n}` or `US {n}` | GitHub → `slug=us-{n}`; `gh issue view` → `github-issue-to-spec.py` → spec |
| `{org}/{project}#{id}` | Azure DevOps → `slug=us-{id}`; REST API → canonical spec |
| `*.spec.md` | local-spec; register directly |
| free-text | brainstorm → `00-write-spec` → `specs/{slug}.spec.md` |

No authenticated source → STOP.

### Step 0 Entry Gate

Before dispatching Step 0 `Task`, the orchestrator asks (AskQuestion, 2 options):

- **I have a US/issue number** (recommended) — user provides GitHub `{n}` or Azure DevOps `{org}/{project}#{id}`
- **I want to describe a feature to brainstorm** — user provides free-text feature description

**If US number**: orch fetches issue, converts to spec, saves to `{us-dir}/{slug}.spec.md`, then dispatches Step 0 `Task` to validate/enrich (optional — can skip directly to Step 1 if spec is complete).

**If feature description**: orch dispatches Step 0 `Task` `00-write-spec` with the description; subagent runs full brainstorming + grilling protocol, writes spec to `specs/{slug}.spec.md`.

After Step 0: spec path registered in state `## Artifacts.specPath`; spec snapshot in `## Artifacts.specSnapshot`.

### Build & Test Validation (7, 10)

Before G2-code commit: [stack.md](stack.md) → build (+ tests unless skip) → Coder fix loop. Stage **only** `src/`, `web/`, `tests/` paths — never `.cursor/plans/`. `skipTests`: `verification.tests: skipped`.

### Integration Validation (11)

`07-integration-validation` via **`Task`**.

| Flag | Effect |
|------|--------|
| `skipIntegration` | no Task; Write skip → step 12 |
| `autoMode` \| `dryRun` | Task without browser; §6 skipped in report |
| normal + gate | `CallMcpTool` cursor-ide-browser |

Gates (normal): **Approve and run test battery** (rec) / **Run without browser** / **Adjust test plan** / **Skip validation** / **Pause workflow**.

Failure (max 3): **Apply fixes and revalidate** (rec) / **Accept with reservations** / **Re-run without fixes** / **Pause**. Fix: G2-code commit only (`src/`/`web/`/`tests/`).

### Workflow Artifact Commit Protocol

| When | Allowed in commit |
|------|-------------------|
| Steps 0–11 | **Code only** under `src/`, `web/`, `tests/` at Steps 7, 10, 11 fix |
| Steps 0–11 | **Forbidden:** `.cursor/plans/**`, `*.plan.exec.md`, `*.exec.dag.json`, `*.report.md`, `*.plan.report.md`, `*.integration-test.*`, `*.state.md`, `*.issue.json` |
| Step 12 | **`{slug}.plan.md`** (checkmarks updated) + **`{slug}.result.md`** — delivery commit via G2-delivery gate |
| Pause | No commit required; **no delete** of any workflow file |

Orchestrator `git add` must be path-scoped — never `git add .` on steps 7/10/11.

### Delivery Result Protocol (Step 12 — before delivery commit)

1. **`Read`** sources: `{slug}.spec.md`, `{slug}.plan.md`, `{slug}.plan.report.md`, `{slug}.report.md`, integration report if exists, `## Open items` in state.
2. **`Write`** `{us-dir}/{slug}.result.md` — brief English summary:

```markdown
# {slug} — Delivery Result

## Expected
<!-- from spec ACs + plan scope (1–3 short paragraphs max) -->

## Done
<!-- from verify report + delivery report + completed DAG tasks (factual, brief) -->

## Next steps
<!-- open items, reservations, manual follow-ups before PR -->

## References
- Spec: {specPath}
- Plan: {slug}.plan.md
- Verify: {slug}.plan.report.md
- Delivery: {slug}.report.md
```

3. **Capture LOC delta:** `Shell` from repo root:
   - Baseline LOC: `git show {baselineCommit}:$(git ls-files src/ web/ tests/ | head -1000 | xargs wc -l 2>/dev/null | tail -1 | awk '{print $1}')` or `git ls-files src/ web/ tests/ | xargs git show {baselineCommit}: 2>/dev/null | wc -l`
   - Final LOC: `git ls-files src/ web/ tests/ | xargs wc -l 2>/dev/null | tail -1 | awk '{print $1}'`
   - Diff stat: `git diff --stat {baselineCommit} -- src/ web/ tests/ | tail -1`
   - Parse added/removed; store in `telemetry.loc`.
4. **Compute benchmark:** aggregate all `telemetry.steps[].elapsedMs` → `totalElapsedMs`; sum all `promptTokens + completionTokens` → `totalTokens`; compute `netDelta = added - removed`.
5. **Append Benchmark section** to `{slug}.result.md` using the [Benchmark report template](#benchmark-report-step-12), populated with computed values and step breakdown table from `telemetry.steps[]`.
6. **Update plan checkmarks:** in `{slug}.plan.md`, mark completed tasks/ACs/checklist items `[x]` per verify report, `completedTasks`, and `completedSteps` ≥5. Use `StrReplace`/`Write`; preserve plan structure.
7. Register `resultSnapshot` + `telemetry.workflowEndedAt` in state `## Artifacts`.
8. **G2-delivery gate** → `Shell` stage only `{slug}.plan.md` + `{slug}.result.md` → `git commit -m "docs({slug}): delivery plan and result"`.
9. Log `step-12-delivery-commit | {sha}` in `## Gate history` and `commits[]`.

`dryRun`: write/simulate result + plan edits + benchmark; no real commit. LOC capture: use current working tree (no baseline diff needed).

### Optional Artifact Cleanup Protocol (Step 12 — after delivery commit)

**Only when workflow completes (`status: completed`) and user explicitly chooses cleanup** — never on **Pause workflow**.

**Gate 1 option "Yes — consolidate…" or dedicated cleanup ask:**

- **Delete temporary artifacts** (rec if user wants lean repo) — `{slug}.plan.exec.md`, `.exec.dag.json`, `.issue.json`, `.plan.report.md`, `.integration-test.*.md`, worktrees, baseline, archive, checkpoint tags
- **Keep all artifacts on disk** (rec if user may re-open or audit) — no delete

**Cleanup execution (when user chooses delete):**

1. **Delete temp files in plan dir:**
   ```bash
   rm {us-dir}/{slug}.plan.exec.md
   rm {us-dir}/{slug}.exec.dag.json
   rm {us-dir}/{slug}.issue.json
   rm {us-dir}/{slug}.plan.report.md
   rm {us-dir}/{slug}.integration-test.plan.md
   rm {us-dir}/{slug}.integration-test.report.md
   ```
2. **Remove checkpoint tags:**
   ```bash
   git tag -l "uswf/{workflow-id}/*" | xargs -r git tag -d
   ```
3. **Remove worktree directories and prune branches:**
   ```bash
   # List worktrees, find branches matching uswf/{workflow-id}/*
   git worktree list | grep "uswf/{workflow-id}" | awk '{print $1}' | while read wt; do
     git worktree remove "$wt" --force 2>/dev/null
   done
   # Delete worktree branches
   git branch -l "uswf/{workflow-id}/*" | sed 's/^[* ]*//' | xargs -r git branch -D
   ```
4. **Remove baseline backup** (if exists):
   ```bash
   rm -rf {us-dir}/{workflow-id}.baseline/
   ```
5. **Remove archive** (if exists):
   ```bash
   rm -rf {us-dir}/{workflow-id}.archive/
   ```

**Preserved (never deleted):** `{slug}.plan.md`, `{slug}.result.md`, `{slug}.spec.md`, `{workflow-id}.state.md` (while `status: active`).

**After cleanup verification:**
```bash
# Confirm no dangling worktrees
git worktree list | grep "uswf/{workflow-id}" && echo "WARN: worktree remains" || echo "Clean"
# Confirm no dangling tags
git tag -l "uswf/{workflow-id}/*" | wc -l | xargs -I{} echo "Tags remaining: {}"
# Confirm no dangling branches
git branch -l "uswf/{workflow-id}/*" | wc -l | xargs -I{} echo "Branches remaining: {}"
```

**Pause / `status: active`:** skip cleanup entirely; all files remain for resume.

**Dry-run:** log intended deletions only; never execute `rm`, `git tag -d`, `git worktree remove`, or `git branch -D`.

### Learning Protocol

**Purpose:** prevent the same mistakes across steps and across workflow runs. MEMORY.md is the persistent anti-regression knowledge base — NOT a changelog.

#### Intra-workflow (step-to-step)

1. **Record:** every subagent writes `step-output.learning` — a list of mistakes made, traps discovered, and constraints found during this step.
2. **Consume:** next step subagent reads `## Workflow memory` and `## Step outputs` in state before acting (see [Memory Consultation](#memory-consultation)).
3. **State as knowledge bus:** `## Workflow memory` accumulates per-step learnings during execution. Orchestrator appends after each step from `step-output.learning`.
4. **Do not repeat:** subagent MUST NOT repeat an approach that a prior step already logged as broken/wrong in `## Workflow memory` or `## Step outputs`.

#### Inter-workflow (MEMORY.md)

5. **Step 12 sweep:** the orchestrator reviews all `## Workflow memory` entries and `step-output.learning` from every step. It promotes generalizable patterns to `MEMORY.md`.
6. **Promotion criteria:**
   - **Technical** — framework/api/pattern-level, not domain-specific
   - **Generalizable** — applies beyond this US/feature
   - **Non-duplicate** — grep `MEMORY.md` first; merge into existing sections if overlapping
   - **Concise** — one line per trap/pattern; minimal prose
7. **MEMORY.md sections:**
   - `## Patterns` — correct approaches, API shapes, EF conventions
   - `## Traps` — wrong approaches, API misuse, broken patterns (do NOT do this)
   - `## Review Patterns` — recurring code review findings
   - `## Index` — grep-friendly keyword index
8. **What NOT to put in MEMORY.md:**
   - Step-by-step logs (that's `CHANGELOG.md`)
   - Domain-specific business rules (that's `CONTEXT.md` or `specs/`)
   - "Worked on X" narratives (that's `CHANGELOG.md`)
   - Duplicates of existing entries
9. **`dryRun`:** never edit `MEMORY.md` — log proposed entries in `## Doc consolidation log` only.

### Telemetry & Benchmarking

Orchestrator records wall-clock time, token usage (reported or estimated), and lines-of-code delta at every step boundary. At Step 12, a consolidated benchmark report is appended to `{slug}.result.md` and the Progress Board.

#### Timing

| Event | Record | Field |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Workflow start | `telemetry.workflowStartedAt` | ISO 8601 timestamp (bootstrap, before Step 0) |
| Step N dispatch | `telemetry.steps[N].dispatchedAt` | ISO 8601 (immediately before `Task` / `Shell`) |
| Step N finish | `telemetry.steps[N].finishedAt` | ISO 8601 (immediately after `Task` / `Shell` returns) |
| Step N elapsed | `telemetry.steps[N].elapsedMs` | `finishedAt - dispatchedAt` (computed, int) |
| Workflow end | `telemetry.workflowEndedAt` | ISO 8601 (Step 12 completion, before cleanup) |
| Total elapsed | `telemetry.totalElapsedMs` | sum of all step `elapsedMs` |

Gate time (AskQuestion waiting) is **excluded** — only agent execution time counts.

#### Token counting

Subagents report token usage in `step-output.telemetry`. The orchestrator aggregates at step finish.

| Field | Source | Fallback |
|-------|--------|----------|
| `promptTokens` | LLM metadata (if subagent returns it) | estimate: prompt chars / 3.5 |
| `completionTokens` | LLM metadata (if subagent returns it) | estimate: completion chars / 3.5 |
| `totalTokens` | `promptTokens + completionTokens` | estimate: (prompt + completion chars) / 3.5 |

Estimate formula: tokenCount ≈ charCount / 3.5 (conservative for mixed code/natural-language text). Labeled `(est.)` in reports when estimated.

For `Shell` steps (7, 12, 13), record elapsed time only; tokens = 0 unless the shell tool emits token metadata.

#### Lines of code delta

At bootstrap (Fase 0) and at Step 12 delivery, count lines across `src/`, `web/`, `tests/`:

```bash
# Lines at start (bootstrap baseline)
git ls-files src/ web/ tests/ | xargs wc -l 2>/dev/null | tail -1

# Lines at end (Step 12, before cleanup)
git diff --stat {baselineCommit} -- src/ web/ tests/ | tail -1
```

Record:

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `telemetry.loc.baseline` | total lines at `baselineCommit` (int) |
| `telemetry.loc.final` | total lines at Step 12 commit (int) |
| `telemetry.loc.added` | `+` lines from `git diff --stat` |
| `telemetry.loc.removed` | `-` lines from `git diff --stat` |
| `telemetry.loc.netDelta` | `added - removed` |

Count only `src/`, `web/`, `tests/` — exclude `.cursor/plans/`, `.agents/`, docs, config files.

#### Step output telemetry contract

Every `step-output` YAML block must include:

```yaml
step-output:
  # ... existing fields ...
  telemetry:
    elapsedMs: {int}
    promptTokens: {int|null}
    completionTokens: {int|null}
    estimated: {boolean}  # true if tokens are estimated, false if from LLM metadata
```

Orchestrator: validate `telemetry` block in `step-output` → merge into state `telemetry.steps[N]`. Missing block → HS-5 (State Hygiene fail).

#### Benchmark report (Step 12)

After `{slug}.result.md` is written, append:

```markdown
## Benchmark

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Total wall-clock time | {h}h {m}m {s}s ({totalElapsedMs}ms agent execution) |
| Steps executed | {N} |
| Total tokens | {sum} (estimated: {bool}) |
| Lines added | +{added} |
| Lines removed | -{removed} |
| Net LOC delta | +{netDelta} |
| Baseline LOC | {baseline} |
| Final LOC | {final} |

### Step breakdown

| Step | Label | Model | Elapsed | Tokens (est.) | Files changed |
|------|-------|-------|---------|---------------|---------------|
| 0 | Spec Creation | {model} | {elapsedMs}ms | {tokens} | {n} |
| 1 | Planning | {model} | {elapsedMs}ms | {tokens} | {n} |
| ... | ... | ... | ... | ... | ... |
```

**Token efficiency:** `tokens/loc` ratio (`totalTokens / netDelta`). Lower = more efficient. **Velocity:** `loc/min` (netDelta / total elapsed minutes). This data enables comparison across workflow runs.

### Step Output Banner

When `autoMode` or `dryRun`, before and after each step:

```markdown
[AUTO] [DRY-RUN] **Starting step {N} {Label}**
[AUTO] **Finished step {N} {Label}**
```

Step 5: one pair per whole step. Print **Finished** on hard stop too.

### Automatic Mode

Parse: `auto` + combinable `dry-run`, `skip-integration`, `skip-tests`, US/spec entry. Also accept legacy `automatico`/`automático` as `auto` flag aliases in input parsing only.

Resume: active `autoMode` same US → continue `currentStep`; else new `workflow-id`, ignore other actives.

| Context | Auto choice (index 0) |
|---------|----------------------|
| Step 0 entry gate | **I have a US/issue number** (user must provide number in invocation) |
| Transition 1–6, 9–10 | **Advance to Step N+1** |
| Transition model change (auto) | **Advance to Step N+1** (keep current model; auto mode cannot switch models mid-flow — use `--model-chain` at invocation or pause to normal mode) |
| Model sub-gate | **Continue with current model** |
| `--model-chain` lookup | auto-applies pre-specified model for this step; overrides index 0 |
| Step 2 needs_user | first option; early → **End refinement and advance** → 2e |
| Step 2e | **I confirm shared understanding — advance to Step 3** |
| Step 7 | **Approve, validate build/tests and commit code** |
| Step 11 skipIntegration | skip step |
| Step 11 plan | **Approve and run test battery without browser** |
| Step 11 failure | **Apply fixes and revalidate** |
| Step 12 delivery | **Commit plan and result** |
| Step 12 cleanup | **Keep all artifacts on disk** (default safe) or delete temps per gate |
| Step 12 §Doc | **Nothing to update / Skip** |
| Step 12 push | **Do not push now** |
| Step 13 gate (fullMode) | **Create PR, monitor, and merge when ready** |

Log `auto-gate | step {N} | {choice} | ISO`. Disabled: backward/repeat/pause menus; Step 3 without shared understanding.

### Checkpoints

Tag `uswf/{workflow-id}/before-step-{N}` = HEAD before step N first mutation. `before-step-1` = `baselineCommit`. Mirror in `checkpoints[]`. Delete on Step 12/reset. Dry-run: log intent only.

### Progress Board

Render: bootstrap/resume; after each step (post-hygiene, pre-gate); pause; `/status`; Step 12 final.

```markdown
## Progress — US {us} (`{workflowId}`)
**Status:** … | **Phase:** {Fx} | **Step:** {N} — {label} | **Branch:** `{branch}` | **Mode:** {autoMode→[AUTO] / dryRun→[DRY-RUN] / fullMode→[FULL] / normal}
**Current model:** {currentModel} | **Step models:** {list from stepModels}

### Pipeline — Phases
- [x] F0 Bootstrap · [ ] F2 Implementation ← **next** …

### Steps (0–12; +13 when fullMode, omit 4/8)
- [x] 0 [{model}] · [x] 1 [{model}] · … · [ ] 5 ← **next** [{currentModel}]

### Refinement _(Step 2 active only)_
Round {r}/3 · blocking: {n}

### Step 3 Execution Mode _(after Step 3)_
**Mode:** {execMode} · {reason}

### Step 5 DAG _(if execMode: parallel)_
- [x] T1 — …
```

Suffixes: `← next` · `⏭ skipped` · `↻ repeating` · `⏮ reopened`. Auto/dry-run: Finished banner → compact board → auto-advance.

**Step 12 final board** — after benchmark computation, append telemetry summary below the board:

```markdown
### Telemetry
| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Total time | {h}h {m}m {s}s ({totalElapsedMs}ms) |
| Total tokens | {tokens} (est: {bool}) |
| Lines +/- | +{added} / -{removed} (net: {netDelta}) |
| Token efficiency | {tokens/loc} tokens/LOC |
| Velocity | {loc/min} LOC/min |
```

### Safe Revert & Backward Navigation

**Revert** = manifest to checkpoint M. Scope: `reset --mixed` → per-path restore from `## Step file log` → remove worktrees ≥M → truncate state <M. Verify `preExistingDirty`. Forbidden: global `reset --hard`, `checkout -- .`, `restore .`, `clean -fd`, stash, push `uswf/*` tags.

**Bootstrap revert data:** `baselineCommit`, `preExistingDirty[]` (`git status --porcelain`), backup `{workflow-id}.baseline/`. Full reset: M=1 + new workflow-id.

**Backward nav** (normal, not auto): Gate **Go back** or Step 7→5 shortcut. Targets: steps 1–3,5–7,9–11 in `completedSteps`. Sub-menu: Planning/Implementation/Review/Validation → confirm → checkpoint revert → redispatch M. Log `backward-nav | from | to | ISO`.

---

## State & dispatch

### `state.md` YAML

```yaml
workflowId, slug, us, specSource, specPath
startedAt, endedAt, status: active|completed|cancelled|failed
currentStep, dryRun, autoMode, skipIntegration, skipTests, fullMode
execMode: sequential|parallel|null  # set after Step 3
branch, baselineCommit, preExistingDirty: []
checkpoints, workflowManifest, commits: [{sha, step, message}]
completedSteps, stepStatus, skippedSteps, completedTasks, stepDispatches
refineRound, currentModel, recommendedModel
stepModels: [{step: N, model: "name", dispatched: ISO}]  # per-step model tracking
modelChain: {stepNumber: "modelName"}  # from --model-chain flag; null if not set
telemetry:
  workflowStartedAt: ISO
  workflowEndedAt: null
  totalElapsedMs: null
  loc:
    baseline: int|null
    final: int|null
    added: int|null
    removed: int|null
    netDelta: int|null
  totalTokens: int|null
  steps: [{ N: int, label: str, dispatchedAt: ISO, finishedAt: ISO, elapsedMs: int, promptTokens: int, completionTokens: int | null, estimated: bool, model: str, filesTouched: int }]
```

Sections: Workflow baseline, manifest, Step file log, Refinement registry, Context, Artifacts, Step outputs, Step model log, Workflow memory, Accumulated decisions, Doc consolidation log, Open items, Gate history.

### Resume / reset

**Auto:** skip Active Resume; use auto resume policy. If existing `active`/`paused` workflow matches same US/slug + `autoMode`, auto-resume.

**Normal — workflow discovery (mandatory before any new workflow):**

1. `Glob` `.cursor/plans/**/*.state.md` → list all state files.
2. For each, `Read` frontmatter YAML: `status`, `workflowId`, `slug`, `us`, `currentStep`, `startedAt`, `autoMode`.
3. Filter: `status: active` or `status: paused`.
4. Present as **selectable workflow list** via AskQuestion:

```text
Found {N} unfinished workflow(s):

1. US {us} — {slug} — Step {currentStep} — started {startedAt} — [{autoMode ? 'AUTO' : 'normal'}] (Recommended)
2. US {us} — {slug} — Step {currentStep} — started {startedAt} — [{autoMode ? 'AUTO' : 'normal'}]
...

Options:
- Resume workflow #1 (Recommended)
- Resume workflow #2
- Start new workflow (ignore existing)
- Cancel for now
```

5. If user picks resume → load state, set `status: active`, skip bootstrap (steps 1–7 in [Bootstrap & Entry](#bootstrap--entry) already done), jump to `currentStep` gate.
6. If paused: resume at same step (checkpoint revert M=currentStep → hygiene → board → gate).
7. If no unfinished workflows found: skip list, proceed directly to bootstrap.

**Full reset:** Checkpoint Revert M=1 → gate **Start again** (new workflow-id) / **Exit**.

**Workflow cleanup for stale state files** (part of new workflow start or explicit request):
- If user starts new workflow while old ones exist, offer: **Archive old workflows** (move state + artifacts to `{workflow-id}.archive/`) / **Delete old workflows** / **Keep both**.
- Stale = `status: active|paused` but `startedAt` older than 7 days → flag in list as `[STALE]`.

### Base Prompt Prefix (`Task` body)

```markdown
# Subagent — Step {STEP} — {Label}
Read state: `.cursor/plans/{slug}/{workflow-id}.state.md`
Skill: {SKILL.md path} — read full.
Orch: us-workflow.md § Step {STEP} · model {currentModel} · {modeFlags}
Enhancing skills (mandatory, always load): karpathy-guidelines, gabarito, caveman
Read: state workflow memory + decisions + doc log; MEMORY.md index; stack.md.
Anchor: uswf/{workflow-id}/before-step-{STEP} @ {sha} · CWD: {repo-root | worktree}
Role: fresh; no resume. files_touched required (revert). model: {currentModel}.
Rules: no `.cursor/plans/` in git-add except Step 12 G2-delivery; needs_user: ≥2 choices, recommended first.
Learning: read ## Workflow memory + ## Step outputs (all prior steps) for traps/errors. Do NOT repeat approaches already logged as broken. Record your own mistakes in step-output.learning.
Telemetry required: record elapsedMs (wall-clock step execution), promptTokens + completionTokens (from LLM metadata if available, else estimate chars/3.5 with estimated: true).
End with ```step-output(status, step, artifacts, files_touched, verification, refine, summary, evidence, decisions, doc_consolidation, needs_user, errors, retry_hint, learning, model, telemetry{elapsedMs, promptTokens|null, completionTokens|null, estimated})
```
```

### Transition Gates

Post-step: hygiene → checkpoint (`Shell` tag) → board → gate.

| Mode | Tool |
|------|------|
| auto | auto-gate table → immediate `Task`/`Shell` |
| normal | **AskQuestion** 5 options → `Task` same turn after answer |

**AskQuestion (normal) — every transition gate, steps 0→1 through 11→12:**

The gate always shows `**Current model:** {currentModel}` and `**Next step:** {N+1} — {Label}`.

- **Advance to Step N+1** (rec) — keep current model `{currentModel}`
- **Switch model and advance** — pick from an explicit list of available model names. The sub-menu lists concrete model names (not classes). Suggested models depend on the next step's role:
  - **Planner/Design** (steps 0–3): thinking/reasoning models (e.g., `gemini-3-pro`, `sonnet-4`, `opus-4.5`)
  - **Coder/Implementation** (steps 5, 10, 11): code-generation models (e.g., `sonnet-4`, `gpt-5.1-codex`, `gemini-3-pro`)
  - **Reviewer/Analysis** (steps 6, 9): thinking models (e.g., `gemini-3-pro`, `sonnet-4`)
  - **General** (step 7, 12, 13): balanced models
  Updates `currentModel` in state; logs `model-change | step {N}→{N+1} | {old} → {new} | {ISO}` in `## Gate history`.
- **Repeat Step N** — revert M=N if partial → `Task`
- **Go back to earlier step** → [Backward Navigation](#backward-navigation)
- **Pause or cancel workflow** → **Pause workflow** (rec on uncertainty — **keeps all artifacts**, `status: active`) / Cancel without revert / Cancel and revert all

**Model switch sub-menu (must include concrete model names, never generic classes):**

```text
Current model: {currentModel}
Next step: {N+1} — {Label}

Choose model for Step {N+1}:
- {model-1} (Recommended)
- {model-2}
- {model-3}
- {model-4}
- Other — type the exact model name
```

The orchestrator knows the available model names from the environment/model registry. If uncertain, present the 4 most common models for the next step's role + "Other" free-text option.

Step 11: **Skip validation**. Step 2: gate 2e before Step 3.

**Model recording per step:** every `## Step outputs ### Step N` block must include `model: {modelName}`. After each step dispatch, append to `## Step model log`:

```markdown
| Step N | {label} | {model} | dispatched {ISO} |
```

State hygiene records model in both the step output block and the step model log table.

---

## Bootstrap & Entry

Before Step 0, the orchestrator initializes:

1. **Config check**: `Shell` `test -f config.json`. If missing:
   - `Shell` `cp config.json.example config.json`
   - AskQuestion (list of fields): **Fill config now** / **Skip — I'll fill manually**
   - If "Fill now": present each top-level section (`project`, `stack`, `domain`, etc.) one at a time, collect values, `Write` to config.json. Skip optional sections user declines.
   - If "Skip": warn that workflow won't have project-specific commands. Proceed.
2. **Parse flags**: `auto`, `dry-run`, `skip-integration`, `skip-tests`, `full`, `--model {name}`, `--model-chain {step:model,...}` from user invocation.
   - `--model {name}` → `currentModel = {name}`
   - `--model-chain` → parse `{step}:{model}` pairs; store in `state.modelChain`. At each transition before step N, check `modelChain[N]`; if present, set `currentModel` automatically and log `model-chain | step {N} | {old} → {new} | ISO` in `## Gate history`.
   - `--model-chain` takes precedence over `--model` at matching steps.
   - Both flags work in **auto mode** (the only way to switch models without pausing).
3. **Auto resume policy** or **Active Resume** (see [Resume / reset](#resume--reset)).
4. **Establish identity**: `workflow-id`, `slug`, `us-dir` from entry.
5. **Baseline**: `Shell` `git status --porcelain` → `preExistingDirty[]`; `git rev-parse HEAD` → `baselineCommit`.
6. **LOC baseline**: `Shell` capture `git ls-files src/ web/ tests/ | xargs wc -l 2>/dev/null | tail -1 | awk '{print $1}'` → `telemetry.loc.baseline`. Store ISO timestamp → `telemetry.workflowStartedAt`.
7. **Checkpoint**: tag `uswf/{workflow-id}/before-step-0`.
8. **Progress Board** render.
9. **Step 0 Entry Gate** → dispatch.

### Step 0 Entry Flow

Orchestrator presents the entry gate (see [Step 0 Entry Gate](#step-0-entry-gate)). After the gate:

**US number provided** (`{n}` for GitHub, `{org}/{project}#{id}` for Azure DevOps):
1. Fetch issue → convert to canonical `*.spec.md` format.
2. Save to `{us-dir}/{slug}.spec.md`.
3. Register `specPath`, `specSource` in state.
4. Skip `Task` dispatch (spec is complete from issue) → proceed to Step 1 gate.

**Feature description provided:**
1. Dispatch `Task` `00-write-spec` with the description and `state.md` path.
2. Subagent runs full brainstorming + grilling protocol (see [`00-write-spec` SKILL.md](../00-write-spec/SKILL.md)).
3. Writes spec to `specs/{slug}.spec.md`.
4. Register `specPath` in state.
5. Proceed to Step 1 gate.

**`*.spec.md` provided** (local spec exists):
1. Use spec as-is; register `specPath`.
2. Skip Step 0 Task dispatch → proceed to Step 1 gate.

## Step instructions

| Step | Action | Artifact |
|------|--------|----------|
| 0 | Entry gate (AskQuestion: US number vs description). If US → fetch + convert to spec. If description → `Task` `00-write-spec` brainstorm + write spec. Register specPath in state. | `{slug}.spec.md` |
| 1 | `Task` `01-plan-us` + specPath | `{slug}.plan.md` |
| 2 | `Task` `02-refine`; FSM 2c/2e; block Step 3 until 2e confirmed | plan in-place |
| 3 | `Task` `03-plan-exec-dag`; memory-conflict first; detect plan size → `execMode: sequential|parallel`. Sequential → skip DAG, proceed. Parallel → DAG generated. | `.plan.exec.md`, `.exec.dag.json` |
| 4† | Model sub-gate F1→F2 in post-3 gate | not in completedSteps |
| 5 | `Task` `04-implement-plan` mode build; worktree. `execMode: sequential` → single Task with `*.plan.md` directly. `execMode: parallel` → DAG ≤3/level (existing). HS-3/4 | verification |
| 6 | `Task` `05-verify-sync-plan-us` readonly | `.plan.report.md` |
| 7 | AskQuestion G2-code → Shell build/test → `git commit` code only `feat(us-{id}): US {id} implementation` | step-7-commit; no `.cursor/plans/` |
| 8† | Model sub-gate F3→F4 post-7 | not in completedSteps |
| 9 | `Task` `06-code-review`; scoped diff stack.md; detect only | score ≥6 or "No feedback" |
| 10 | `Task` `04-implement-plan` mode fix; G2-code only; `.report.md` on disk uncommitted | HS-3/4 |
| 11 | skipIntegration→Write skip; else `Task` integration-validation; browser if gated | reports on disk uncommitted |
| 12 | [Delivery Result Protocol](#delivery-result-protocol-step-12--before-delivery-commit) → LOC capture + benchmark → G2-delivery commit → optional [cleanup](#optional-artifact-cleanup-protocol-step-12--after-delivery-commit). `status: completed` unless `fullMode` (continues to Step 13). | `{slug}.result.md` + benchmark |
| 13 | `fullMode` only. Gate: create PR + monitor / push only / skip. `Task` or `Shell` `11-ship-pr`: push → create PR → goal-fix-pr (5m, max 10) → merge when activeThreads==0. | PR URL, merge commit |

Post-mutating step: merge files_touched → Step file log; backup preExistingDirty; checkpoint `before-step-{N+1}`.

### Step 12 gates & cleanup

**Order:** Delivery Result Protocol → G2-delivery commit → MEMORY.md sweep → cleanup gate → §Doc → push consent (replaced by Step 13 gate when `fullMode`).

**MEMORY.md sweep (mandatory, before cleanup gate):**
1. `Read` all `## Workflow memory` entries and `step-output.learning` from every step in state.
2. Filter: keep only generalizable, technical, non-duplicate entries.
3. Discard: domain-specific rules, "worked on X", changelog narratives.
4. `Grep` `MEMORY.md` for existing coverage of each candidate.
5. `Write`/`StrReplace` new entries under `## Traps`, `## Patterns`, or `## Review Patterns`.
6. Update `## Index` with new keywords.
7. Log entries in `## Doc consolidation log`: `| MEMORY.md | {section} | {summary} | Step 12 sweep |`.
8. `dryRun`: skip write; log proposed entries only.

**G2-delivery:** **Commit plan and result** (rec) — stage `{slug}.plan.md` + `{slug}.result.md` only. / **Skip**.
**Gate 1:** **Consolidate docs + clean temps** (rec) — optional delete / **Docs only** / **Skip**.
**Gate 2 §Doc:** **Update now** / **Skip**.
**Cleanup:** only Gate 1 opt-in; never on pause. Execution follows [Cleanup Protocol](#optional-artifact-cleanup-protocol-step-12--after-delivery-commit): delete `.plan.exec.md`, `.exec.dag.json`, worktrees, git tags (`uswf/*`), baseline, archive. Never `{slug}.plan.md`, `{slug}.result.md`, `{workflow-id}.state.md` while active.

Push consent: **Do not push now** — tags never pushed.

### Step 13 — Ship & PR (`fullMode` only)

After Step 12, orch presents ship gate. Pipeline: push → create PR → goal-fix-pr loop → merge.

**Gate (normal):** **Create PR, monitor, merge** (rec) / **Push only** / **Skip**. Auto: option 0. Dry-run: simulate.

**Pipeline (Create PR + monitor):**
1. `git push -u origin {branch}` (skip if already pushed).
2. `gh pr create --head {branch} --base {baseBranch}`. Reuse existing open PR.
3. Dispatch `11-ship-pr` skill ([SKILL.md](../11-ship-pr/SKILL.md)): 300s initial wait → heartbeat: fetch threads → solve-pr if `activeThreads>0` → commit → resolve → push → 120s wait. Max 10 iterations. Convergence → `gh pr checks --watch` → `gh pr merge --merge`. Never `--delete-branch` when head is `develop`.
4. auto: auto-selects merge option, skill auto-gates per `09-goal-fix-pr`.

**Output:** `step-output` with `pr: {number, url, state}`, `goalFixPr: {iterations, max, activeThreadsRemaining, merged}`.
**Stop:** max exhausted · merge blocked · cancelled · PR closed.

---

## Error policy

Retry: max 3; backoff 0s→30s→60s. Revert: Checkpoint Algorithm only. Conduct: 4/8 no Task; orch never implements code; fresh Task/step; max 1 worktree; G2-code steps 7/10/11; G2-delivery step 12; HS-2a blocks plan-dir commits mid-workflow.

## Post-workflow (outside this agent)

Manual QA **after** workflow completion (or pause before Step 12) is **not** resumed here. Use standalone skill [`step-10-update-plan-implementation`](../10-update-plan-implementation/SKILL.md) (`/step-10`) — append plan §9, implement delta, update `{slug}.result.md`, certify for PR. Distinct from **Step 10** above (in-pipeline review fixes).

## Triggers

```
@[us-workflow] [auto|dry-run|skip-integration|skip-tests|full] [--model {name}] [--model-chain step:model,...] [US {issue_id} | {org}/{project}#{id} | {name}.spec.md | "feature description"]
/us-workflow [flags] [US {issue_id} | {org}/{project}#{id} | {name}.spec.md | "feature description"]
/status | progress | where am I? → Progress Board only
go back | change plan | back to step X → Backward Nav (not in auto)
switch model | change model → mid-workflow model switch (normal mode only — presented at every transition gate)
```

**Model flags:**

| Flag | Argument | Effect |
|------|----------|--------|
| `--model` | `{name}` | Set `currentModel` at workflow start. Overrides default/previous model. |
| `--model-chain` | `{step}:{model},{step}:{model},...` | Pre-specify models per step. Orchestrator switches automatically at each step boundary. Overrides individual `--model`. Example: `--model-chain 5:sonnet-4,9:gemini-3-pro,10:sonnet-4` |

`--model-chain` is the only way to switch models in **auto mode**. In normal mode, the user can also switch at any transition gate via the **Switch model and advance** option. If a step in the chain has no mapping, the current model persists from the previous step.

If invoked **without** a US number, spec path, or description, the orchestrator asks:
> **Give me the US number (Azure DevOps or GitHub) or write your feature description to start brainstorming and write the spec.**

Combinable flags. Examples:
- `/us-workflow auto skip-tests skip-integration US 1234`
- `/us-workflow --model sonnet-4 "Implement a product analytics dashboard with real-time charts"`
- `/us-workflow auto contoso/project#5678`
- `/us-workflow full US 99`
- `/us-workflow auto --model-chain 5:sonnet-4,9:gemini-3-pro,10:sonnet-4 US 1234`
- `/us-workflow --model sonnet-4 auto skip-tests US 567`
